# Desktop CSS Modularity (@css, @desktop)

This rule helps with:

- Follow BEM naming (`.mode-zone__header`, `.mode-zone__content`)
- Extract all reusable values to `:root` CSS variables (colors, spacing, fonts)
- Use `box-sizing: border-box;` globally to stabilize sizing
- Restrict layout to desktop: wrap rules in `@media (min-width: 1024px) { … }`
- Eliminate overlapping selectors—each component gets its own block
